        <h1>About GreenSteps</h1>
        <section>
            <h2>Our Mission</h2>
            <p>At GreenSteps, we believe that small, everyday choices can lead to a significant positive impact on both personal health and the environment. Our goal is to empower individuals by providing them with the tools to track their travel habits, reduce carbon emissions, and improve their well-being through active transportation.</p>
        </section>
        
        <section>
            <h2>Who We Are</h2>
            <p>GreenSteps was created by a team of sustainability advocates and tech enthusiasts who wanted to bridge the gap between technology and environmental awareness. We are dedicated to making sustainable living accessible and rewarding for everyone.</p>
        </section>
        
        <section>
            <h2>What We Offer</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Impact Tracking: Measure the carbon emissions you save and the calories you burn with every trip.</li>
                <li>Real-Time Analytics: Get instant feedback on your choices to stay informed and motivated.</li>
                <li>Goal Setting & Achievements: Challenge yourself with milestones and celebrate your progress.</li>
                <li>Educational Resources: Learn practical tips to enhance your sustainable lifestyle.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        
        <section>
            <h2>Why It Matters</h2>
            <p>Transportation is one of the largest contributors to carbon emissions globally. By making conscious decisions like walking, biking, or using public transit, individuals can significantly reduce their environmental impact. GreenSteps provides a simple, engaging way to visualize these benefits and encourage more sustainable habits.</p>
        </section>
        
        <section>
            <h2>Join Us</h2>
            <p>Be a part of the movement towards a greener future. Start tracking your journey with GreenSteps and take a step towards a healthier planet and a healthier you.</p>
        </section>
